abstract: >-
  This paper analyzes cryptographic methods for selective disclosure in verifiable credentials, specifically comparing commitment-based approaches (like ISO/IEC 18013-5) against zero-knowledge proof methods (like BBS signatures). Through a combination of theoretical analysis and Rust-based experimental evaluation, it highlights the trade-offs between performance, standardization, and privacy features such as unlinkability and quantum safety.
